Adds a bcr_test_module/ subdirectory to use as a root module in the BCR
presubmit anonymous-module test.

Why this is needed: rules_jvm_external resolves a single `maven` repo across
all bzlmod modules contributing to it. Protobuf 31.0+ declares
`lock_file = "//:maven_install.json"` on its `maven.install`, while
grpc-java's does not. When the root module is empty (the BCR anonymous test
just does `bazel_dep(name = "grpc-java", version = "1.80.0")`), the final
`@maven` repo gets hydrated only from protobuf's lock_file, silently dropping
all of grpc-java's artifacts (animal-sniffer, netty, opencensus, ...).

Per rules_jvm_external's merge logic, the root module's lock_file always
wins. By using bcr_test_module as the root and giving it its own
`maven.install` with a lock_file that resolves the merged artifact set, the
generated `@maven` repo contains everything both modules contribute, and
`@grpc-java//:java_grpc_library__external_repo_test` builds successfully.

End users who already have their own `maven.install` with a lock_file in
their root MODULE.bazel are unaffected — their lock_file wins instead.
--- /dev/null
+++ b/bcr_test_module/MODULE.bazel
@@ -0,0 +1,17 @@
+module(name = "bcr_test_module", version = "0.0.0")
+
+bazel_dep(name = "grpc-java", version = "1.80.0")
+local_path_override(
+    module_name = "grpc-java",
+    path = "..",
+)
+
+bazel_dep(name = "rules_jvm_external", version = "6.0")
+
+maven = use_extension("@rules_jvm_external//:extensions.bzl", "maven")
+maven.install(
+    lock_file = "//:maven_install.json",
+    repositories = ["https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/"],
+    strict_visibility = True,
+)
+use_repo(maven, "maven", "unpinned_maven")
--- /dev/null
